    • Method Detail

      • addToMap

        public abstract void addToMap​(ECUInitializer eI)
        All child classes will have an addToMap method that is called in child class constructors. This child class constructor must be instantiated with a reference to an ECUInitializer.
        Parameters:
        eI - Reference to an ECUInitializer Object

      • report

        public abstract java.lang.String report​()
        Generic getter method
        Returns:
        Value the sensor is responsible for monitoring (ie. rpm for EngineSpeed).

      • write

        public byte[] write​(byte[] mess)
        Generates a message that can be sent to the ECU. The message sent to the write method should only contain in the following order the Data Size, Command/Response, and the Data bytes.
        Parameters:
        mess - Byte array containing the message to be written to the ECU
        Returns:
        Formatted message to be sent to the ECU

      • getAddress

        public abstract java.lang.String getAddress​()
        All sensors are created and placed into a HashMap, accessible only through the ECUInitializer. Keys are String objects unique to all sensors.
        Returns:
        String key used to access correct object in ECUInitializer map

      • parsedResponse

        protected byte[] parsedResponse​(byte[] response)
        Returns a formatted response that removes duplicate information leaving only data.
        Parameters:
        response - Full response given by ECU
        Returns:
        Response without the initial, source, target and checksum bytes
